<DOC><DOCNO> AP890405-0178 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-05-89 1739EDT</FILEID><FIRST>u i AM-Chad-FailedCoup     04-05 0185</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Chad-Failed Coup,0195</SECOND><HEAD>Chad Officials Reported Arrested After Coup Attempt</HEAD><DATELINE>N'DJAMENA, Chad (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   One top-ranking government official wasarrested, one fled and another was missing after participating in aweekend coup attempt against the government of President HisseneHabre, diplomats said Wednesday.   People trying to enter or leave the capital were stopped atmilitary roadblocks, according to sources who asked not to beidentified.   Interior Minister Mahamat Itno was arrested after Saturday'sunsuccessful coup, while Army commander, Hassan Djamous fledN'Djamena and the president's military adviser, Idriss Debi, wasmissing, sources said.   A Chadian nationalist group issued a statement in Brussels,Belgium Wednesday, saying mass arrests were occurring in thecapital.   Itno, Djamous and Debi reportedly staged the coup after Habre'sAnakaza tribe attempted to take key government administrative andmilitary posts. The officials hoped to maintain the Hadjarai andZakawa tribes in the government, sources said.   In November 1987, Habre signed a peace pact in Baghdad, Iraq,with former rebel leader Ibn Omar, who was appointed foreignminister earlier this year.   The pact led to the government's reconciliation with numerouspolitical opponents.</TEXT></DOC>